Locale manager for Wine
WineLocale clones the functionality of Microsoft AppLocale in Wine. It is used to manage global locale settings and font settings in the Wine registry to ensure proper display of non-Latin type in pre-Unicode portable executables.
Currently supported languages include:
* ar - Arabic
* en - English
* el_GR - Hebrew
* ja_JP - Japanese
* ko_KR - Korean
* ru_RU - Russian
* zh_CN - Chinese
* zh_TW - Chinese (Traditional)
Capable of operating in both console and GUI modes.
